              "path": "05-marketing/outreach-templates/template-A-influencer.md",
              "content": "# Outreach Template A — Food Influencer / Creator\n\n**Use for:** YouTube food creators, Instagram cooking influencers, TikTok food personalities  \n**Tone:** Direct, peer-to-peer, no corporate language  \n**Send via:** DM (Instagram/YouTube) or email if available\n\n---\n\n## DM Version (Instagram/TikTok — short form)\n\nSubject: n/a (DM)\n\nHey [Name],\n\nQuick one — I make a Dutch oven with a drain in the bottom of the pot. Designed specifically for people who fry in tallow and want to keep and reuse the fat safely.\n\nM18×1.5 drain plug, copper crush washer, 12\" T-handle wrench, stainless catcher with mirror-polished interior. Full system. Zero plastic.\n\nGenuinely think your audience would find it interesting. Would love to send you one to test — no obligation, no script, just honest use. If you like it, say so. If you don't, say that too.\n\nInterested?\n\n— [Name]  \nTallow Native\n\n---\n\n## Email Version (longer, for email outreach)\n\n**Subject:** Tallow Dutch oven with a drain port — want to test it?\n\nHi [First Name],\n\nI'm [Name], founder of Tallow Native. We make a Dutch oven with a precision drain port in the bottom of the pot — designed for people who fry in beef tallow, lard, and other animal fats.\n\nThe short version: the drain port uses an M18×1.5 thread (automotive oil drain plug specification) and a copper crush washer seal. You lower a 12-inch T-handle wrench through the hot fat, turn counterclockwise, and the fat drains clean through a 150-micron stainless filter into a mirror-polished stainless catcher below. No pouring, no burning, no wasted fat.\n\nI've been following your content for [X time] and I think your audience would find this genuinely useful — not because it's a product, but because the problem it solves is real and the engineering is interesting.\n\nI'd like to send you a complete system to test. No commitment, no scripted review. If it works for you, I'd love it if you shared it. If it doesn't, honest feedback is more useful to me than a polite silence.\n\nThe first production run is [DATE]. I can have a unit to you by [DATE].\n\nInterested? Just reply to this email and I'll get the shipping details from you.\n\nThank you for your time.\n\n— [Name]  \nTallow Native  \npress@tallownative.com  \ntallownative.com\n\n---\n\n## Follow-Up (if no response after 10 days)\n\nHi [Name] — quick follow-up on the tallow Dutch oven. Happy to answer any questions about the product if you'd like to know more before deciding. Otherwise, understood if it's not a fit.\n\n— [Name]\n"
