              "path": "05-marketing/outreach-templates/template-E-collab.md",
              "content": "# Outreach Template E — Collaboration / Co-Marketing\n\n**Use for:** Tallow producers, specialty food brands, butcher shops, complementary products  \n**Tone:** Partnership-minded, mutually beneficial\n\n---\n\n**Subject:** Co-marketing idea — Tallow Native + [Their Brand]\n\nHi [Name],\n\nI'm [Founder Name], the founder of Tallow Native — a new cookware brand launching a Dutch oven designed specifically for people who fry in beef tallow. The pot has a drain port in the bottom that lets users drain, filter, and store hot tallow safely using a stainless catcher system.\n\nI'm reaching out because there's an obvious connection between what you do (making/selling quality tallow) and what we make (the tool for using it properly). Your customers are exactly our customers.\n\nI have a few collaboration ideas in mind:\n\n**Option 1 — Bundling:** Include a Tallow Native product card or discount code with your tallow orders. We'd reciprocate by recommending your tallow to our customers.\n\n**Option 2 — Co-marketing:** A joint email or social post targeting people who buy quality tallow. We explain the tool; you explain the fat. Shared audience, no cost.\n\n**Option 3 — Gift/Launch Package:** A \"complete tallow frying starter kit\" — your tallow + our system — sold or promoted together.\n\nNo obligation on any of these. Happy to start a conversation and see what makes sense for both brands.\n\nIf you'd like to try the system yourself first, I'm happy to send one to your team. You should know what you're recommending.\n\n— [Founder Name]  \nTallow Native  \nhello@tallownative.com | tallownative.com\n"
