          "content": "# Tallow Native — 60-Second Product Demo Video Script\n\n**Version:** 1.0 | **Format:** Voiceover + cooking footage  \n**Tone:** Direct, confident, no hype  \n**Use:** YouTube pre-roll, website hero video, product page\n\n---\n\n## VIDEO SCRIPT — 60 SECONDS\n\n**[OPENING SHOT: Close-up of cast iron pot on a gas burner. Fat is at temperature — you can see the shimmer. Food is being pulled from the fat with a spider strainer. Sound: crackling fat, no music yet.]**\n\n**VOICEOVER (calm, direct):**  \nYou just made the best fried chicken of your life.\n\n**[CUT TO: Wide shot of the pot on the burner. Fat level visible. 375°F reading on thermometer in frame.]**\n\n**VOICEOVER:**  \nSix pounds of tallow. Four hundred dollars of groceries. A perfect batch.\n\n**[BEAT. Pause for effect.]**\n\n**VOICEOVER:**  \nNow deal with the fat.\n\n**[CUT TO: Close-up on the bottom of the pot. Exterior funnel visible. The drain port and its copper-colored center.]**\n\n**VOICEOVER:**  \nThis is the Tallow Native Dutch Oven.  \nIt has a drain port in the bottom.\n\n**[CUT TO: Tallow Catcher being positioned below the pot on the counter. It clicks into alignment with the pot's funnel.]**\n\n**VOICEOVER:**  \nPosition the catcher.\n\n**[CUT TO: Close-up of the T-handle hex wrench being lowered through the hot fat — smooth, deliberate. The user's hands stay at the top of the 12-inch handle, well above the pot rim.]**\n\n**VOICEOVER:**  \nLower the wrench.\n\n**[CUT TO: Close-up of the hex bit engaging the drain plug socket. User's wrist rotates counterclockwise — firm, one motion.]**\n\n**VOICEOVER:**  \nTurn.\n\n**[CUT TO: External shot of the pot bottom. Tallow flowing clean and gold through the funnel and down into the catcher below. The filter is visible. The fat is clean.]**\n\n**[MUSIC enters: low, warm, slightly industrial. Not dramatic — grounded.]**\n\n**VOICEOVER:**  \nHot tallow. Through the filter. Into the catcher.  \nSixty seconds for a full pot.\n\n**[CUT TO: Refrigerator shot. Catcher with storage lid on, sitting on a shelf. Tallow solidifying, visible through the catcher top.]**\n\n**VOICEOVER:**  \nSeal it. Refrigerate it.\n\n**[CUT TO: Time-lapse or cut of the solid tallow puck: white-gold, clean, ready.]**\n\n**[CUT TO: The catcher inverted over the pot. A hand presses the small silicone vent button. A beat. Then the solid tallow puck drops cleanly into the pot.]**\n\n**VOICEOVER:**  \nNext session: invert the catcher.  \nPress the vent button.  \nThe puck drops.\n\n**[Beat. One clean product shot — Dutch oven with the lid on, catcher beside it, T-handle wrench laying horizontally. All matte black, cream, stainless. Clean composition.]**\n\n**VOICEOVER:**  \nZero plastic. M18×1.5 drain port.  \nStainless. Copper. Cast iron. Silicone.\n\n**[Text on screen: TALLOW NATIVE]**\n**[Text on screen: tallownative.com]**\n\n**VOICEOVER:**  \nFor people who fry in tallow.\n\n**[Fade to black. Logo on cream background. No music end swell — let it go quiet.]**\n\n**[END CARD: \"TALLOW NATIVE\" wordmark + tagline \"Built for the fryer.\" + URL]**\n\n---\n\n## PRODUCTION NOTES\n\n**Total runtime target:** 58–62 seconds (adjust VO pacing as needed)\n\n**Shot list required:**\n1. Close-up: food being removed from hot tallow (spider/slotted spoon)\n2. Wide: pot on burner, thermometer in fat, fat level visible\n3. Close-up: exterior pot bottom, drain funnel, drain plug visible\n4. Action: Tallow catcher being placed below the pot\n5. Action: T-handle wrench being lowered through hot fat (glass side-wall if possible for transparency)\n6. Close-up: hex bit engaging drain plug socket\n7. Action: Tallow flowing through funnel into catcher\n8. Close-up: fat passing through 150µm filter mesh (macro lens)\n9. Interior fridge: catcher with lid on, tallow solidifying\n10. Close-up: solid tallow puck in catcher (cream/white, clean)\n11. Action: Catcher inverted over pot; vent button pressed; puck drops\n12. Product still: Full system flat lay or grouped beauty shot\n\n**Music:** Recommend temp track: low-key, confident. No sizzle-music clichés. Think Rogue One trailer vibe, much quieter. Instrumental.\n\n**VO talent:** Someone who sounds like they cook. Not a pitch voice. A peer.\n\n**No graphics/animations needed** — the product is visual enough. Keep it as documentary as possible.\n"
