          "path": "06-packaging/box-dieline.md",
          "content": "# Tallow Native — Product Packaging Design Specification (Box Dieline)\n\n**Version:** 1.0 | **Date:** February 2026\n\n---\n\n## 1. Packaging Structure Overview\n\nThe Tallow Native Dutch Oven System uses a two-box system:\n\n1. **Inner box (Retail/Gift box):** Rigid set-up box (lid-off-base style). Primary retail presentation. Holds all product components.\n2. **Outer box (Shipping box):** Corrugated E-flute shipping carton with 1\" padding clearance on all sides.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Inner Box (Rigid Set-Up Box)\n\n### Structure\n**Type:** Lid-off-base (telescope box). The lid is a shallow tray that slides off the base — like a high-end shoe box or premium electronics packaging.\n\n**Construction:** Rigid chipboard (2mm greyboard) wrapped in uncoated paper. Exterior paper is printed offset (4-color CMYK). Interior is lined with uncoated cream paper.\n\n### Dimensions\n\n| Component | Width | Length | Height |\n|-----------|-------|--------|--------|\n| Box base | 13 in (330mm) | 13 in (330mm) | 10 in (254mm) |\n| Box lid | 13.25 in (337mm) | 13.25 in (337mm) | 1.5 in (38mm) |\n| Box total (closed) | 13.25 in (337mm) | 13.25 in (337mm) | 11.5 in (292mm) |\n\n**Interior clear dimensions (base):**\n- Width: 12.75 in (324mm)\n- Length: 12.75 in (324mm)\n- Depth: 10 in (254mm)\n\n### Interior Liner / Insert System\n\nAll inserts are **formed recycled-pulp trays** (molded fiber, no plastic, natural gray color).\n\n**Layer 1 — Top (accessible when lid is removed):**\n- Formed pulp insert holds the Dutch oven lid (enameled CI) in the center\n- Three accessory depressions beside the lid: T-handle wrench (in a diagonal channel), accessory bag (square depression), and recipe card + manuals (flat layer)\n- Tissue paper sheet (unbleached, cream) covers this layer\n\n**Layer 2 — Middle:**\n- Formed pulp tray holding the tallow catcher (inverted, narrow end up)\n- Depression sized to hold catcher body diameter at mid-height\n- Catcher sits upright with storage lid already installed\n\n**Layer 3 — Bottom:**\n- Formed pulp base supporting the Dutch oven body\n- Dutch oven sits upright, right-side-up\n- Centered in base tray, walls contact the exterior sides of the pot\n- Accessory bag (with 5 crush washers + cheesecloth rings) sits inside the pot itself\n\n**Note:** User opens box, removes tissue layer, sees the Dutch oven lid, T-handle wrench, and materials. Below that, catcher and pot. Intentional reveal sequence.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Outer Shipping Box\n\n**Structure:** Regular slotted container (RSC), E-flute corrugated\n\n**Interior dimensions:**  \n- 15 in (381mm) × 15 in (381mm) × 14 in (356mm)\n\n**Exterior dimensions:**  \n- 15.25 in (387mm) × 15.25 in (387mm) × 14.25 in (362mm) (add board thickness ~0.125 in each side)\n\n**Cushioning:** Crinkled recycled paper void fill (no plastic peanuts, no bubble wrap) in the 1\" gap between inner and outer box on all sides.\n\n**Closure:** Hot melt adhesive flap seal (standard RSC closure). Branded kraft tape seal over flap (optional for premium feel).\n\n**Print:** 2-color flexo print on kraft (natural brown). Prints on top face and one long side face only.\n- Face 1 (top): Tallow Native wordmark + \"Tallow Native Dutch Oven System\" text\n- Face 2 (long side): \"Built for the fryer. Handle with care.\" + brand wordmark\n- Interior: Unprinted kraft\n\n---\n\n## 4. Dieline Specifications\n\n**Inner box base dieline:**\n\n```\nDIELINE ORIENTATION: Score lines = dashes; Cut lines = solid\n\n                    ←————— 13.0\" ——————→\n         ┌──────────────────────────────────┐  ↑\n         │                                  │  │\n         │  FRONT PANEL (printed)           │ 10\" (box height / depth)\n         │  TALLOW NATIVE                   │  │\n         │  [logo + artwork]                │  │\n         │                                  │  ↓\n         └──────────────────────────────────┘\n         \nWrapped in printed paper. Scored and folded by box manufacturer.\nBase: 13.0 × 13.0 × 10.0 in interior\nLid: 13.25 × 13.25 × 1.5 in interior\n\nChipboard: 2mm greyboard\nPaper wrap: 128gsm coated on face; 80gsm uncoated on interior\nFinish: Soft-touch matte laminate on exterior (outside of lid and base exterior)\n```\n\n**Outer box (RSC) dieline:**\n\n```\n            ←—— 15.0\" ——→\n            \n            ↑ Flap: 7.5\" deep\n            │ (overlapping, top and bottom)\n            │\n  ┌─────────┴─────────┐\n  │  ← 14.0\" height  │\n  │                   │\n  │   TALLOW NATIVE   │\n  │  (2-color print)  │  ←─── Side face A (long, 15\")\n  │                   │\n  └─────────┬─────────┘\n            │\n            ↓ Flap: 7.0\" deep\n\nWidth: 15.0\"\nLength: 15.0\"  \nHeight: 14.0\"\nWall: E-flute corrugated (~0.060\" thick)\nPrint: Brown kraft, 2-color water-based flexo\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. Weight and Shipping Specs\n\n| Package | Weight |\n|---------|--------|\n| Inner rigid box (empty) | 220g (0.49 lbs) |\n| Outer shipping box (empty) | 380g (0.84 lbs) |\n| Pulp inserts | 145g (0.32 lbs) |\n| Product + accessories | 5,063g (11.16 lbs) |\n| Documentation | 71g (0.16 lbs) |\n| Tissue / void fill | 120g (0.26 lbs) |\n| **TOTAL SHIP WEIGHT** | **~5,999g (~13.22 lbs)** |\n\n**Dimensional weight (UPS/FedEx):**  \n15.25 × 15.25 × 14.25 in = 3,314 in³ ÷ 139 = **23.8 lbs dim weight**  \n→ Customer is charged for dimensional weight; actual weight is lighter.\n\n---\n\n*End of Box Dieline Specification — Version 1.0*\n"
