          "type": "md",
          "path": "07-business/pre-order-terms.md",
          "content": "# Tallow Native — Pre-Order Terms and Conditions\n\n**Effective Date:** [DATE]  \n**Company:** Tallow Native LLC, [City], Texas\n\n---\n\n## 1. Acceptance of Terms\n\nBy placing a pre-order for the Tallow Native Dutch Oven System (\"Product\") through tallownative.com (\"Site\"), you (\"Customer\") agree to these Pre-Order Terms and Conditions (\"Terms\"). Please read these Terms carefully before completing your pre-order.\n\n---\n\n## 2. What Is a Pre-Order?\n\nA pre-order is a reservation for the Product, which is not yet available for immediate shipment. Pre-orders are taken prior to the first production run shipping. By placing a pre-order, you are reserving a unit from the first production run and will be charged at the time of the pre-order (or at the time of shipment, depending on the checkout configuration in effect at the time of your order).\n\n---\n\n## 3. Estimated Ship Date\n\nThe estimated ship date for the first production run is **[ESTIMATED SHIP DATE]**. This date is an estimate only. Tallow Native LLC does not guarantee delivery by this date. Actual ship dates may vary due to manufacturing delays, shipping delays, customs clearance, force majeure events, or other circumstances beyond Tallow Native's reasonable control.\n\n**Tallow Native will communicate promptly** if the estimated ship date changes materially (defined as a delay of more than 30 days from the estimate at the time of order).\n\n---\n\n## 4. Pre-Order Payment\n\n**Payment is collected at the time of pre-order.** Your payment method will be charged when you complete checkout. By placing a pre-order, you authorize Tallow Native to charge your payment method for the full purchase price plus applicable taxes and shipping fees.\n\n**Price guarantee:** The price displayed at the time of pre-order is the price you will pay. Tallow Native will not charge additional amounts after checkout.\n\n**Payment methods:** Credit card, debit card, and other payment methods as offered at checkout. All transactions processed securely via [Payment Processor, e.g., Stripe / Shopify Payments].\n\n---\n\n## 5. Shipping\n\n**Pre-orders include free standard shipping** to addresses in the continental United States. Alaska, Hawaii, and international addresses are not eligible for pre-order at this time.\n\n**Shipping method:** Ground shipping (UPS, FedEx, or USPS at Tallow Native's discretion). Tracking information will be provided when your order ships.\n\n**Signature requirement:** Due to the value and weight of the Product, signature confirmation on delivery may be required.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Pre-Order Cancellations\n\n**By the Customer:** You may cancel your pre-order for a full refund at any time before your order ships. To cancel, email support@tallownative.com with your order number and the subject line \"Pre-Order Cancellation.\" Refunds will be processed within 5–10 business days to your original payment method.\n\n**By Tallow Native:** Tallow Native reserves the right to cancel pre-orders and issue full refunds if production cannot be completed, the product design changes materially, or for other reasons at our discretion. In such cases, you will be notified promptly and refunded in full.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Post-Shipment Returns\n\nOnce your order has shipped, the standard **60-day return policy** applies (see Warranty document for details). You have 60 days from the date of delivery to return the Product for a full refund, no questions asked, as long as:\n- You have actually used the product (we want you to try it; unopened returns are also accepted)\n- You ship it back in the original packaging (or comparable protection)\n- You contact support@tallownative.com to initiate the return\n\nReturn shipping is at the customer's expense except in cases of defective product or our error.\n\n---\n\n## 8. Product Description\n\nThe Product is the Tallow Native Dutch Oven System as described on tallownative.com at the time of pre-order. Minor design changes may occur between the time of pre-order and delivery. Tallow Native will notify customers of any material changes (defined as changes affecting core functionality, materials, or primary specifications).\n\n---\n\n## 9. Warranty\n\nThe Product is covered by a **one-year limited warranty** against manufacturing defects. Full warranty terms are available at tallownative.com/warranty. The warranty does not affect your statutory rights.\n\n---\n\n## 10. Limitation of Liability\n\nTo the maximum extent permitted by applicable law, Tallow Native's liability for any claim arising out of a pre-order is limited to the total amount paid by you for your pre-order. Tallow Native is not liable for indirect, incidental, special, or consequential damages.\n\n---\n\n## 11. Governing Law\n\nThese Terms are governed by the laws of the State of Texas, without regard to conflict of law provisions. Any disputes shall be resolved in the state or federal courts located in [County], Texas.\n\n---\n\n## 12. Contact\n\n**Support:** support@tallownative.com  \n**Mailing:** Tallow Native LLC, [Address], [City], TX [ZIP]\n\n---\n\n*By completing your pre-order, you confirm that you have read and agree to these Terms.*\n\n*Last updated: [DATE]*\n"
