          "content": "# Tallow Native — Product Warranty\n\n**Effective Date:** [DATE]  \n**Issuing Company:** Tallow Native LLC, [City], Texas\n\n---\n\n## Tallow Native Dutch Oven System — One-Year Limited Warranty\n\nTallow Native LLC (\"Tallow Native,\" \"we,\" \"us\") warrants that the Tallow Native Dutch Oven System (\"Product\") will be free from manufacturing defects in materials and workmanship for **one (1) year** from the date of original purchase (\"Warranty Period\").\n\n---\n\n## What Is Covered\n\nThis warranty covers defects arising from the manufacturing process, including:\n\n**Dutch Oven:**\n- Enamel chipping or crazing that results from a manufacturing defect (not from physical impact, dropping, or thermal shock from user error)\n- Structural cracks in the cast iron body not caused by impact or misuse\n- Failure of the drain boss threads (such that the drain plug cannot be properly seated) due to manufacturing defect\n- Drain plug that leaks when correctly installed with a fresh crush washer and proper torque (see product manual)\n- Lid gasket that fails to seal under normal use within the warranty period\n- Vent plug O-ring that fails to seal under normal use within the warranty period\n\n**Tallow Catcher:**\n- Weld failure at any joint in the catcher, funnel, or bottom plate\n- Mirror finish degradation caused by manufacturing defect (not cleaning practices or abrasion)\n- Vent hole deformation preventing proper button installation\n\n**Accessories:**\n- T-handle wrench that breaks under normal use torque loads\n- Drain plug thread deformation (when defect occurs before reasonable use)\n- Mesh filter disc that tears or deforms without physical damage from user\n\n---\n\n## What Is NOT Covered\n\nThis warranty does not cover:\n\n- Damage resulting from dropping, impact, or mishandling\n- Enamel chips caused by physical impact (dropping, utensil strikes, contact with hard surfaces)\n- Damage from heating the pot empty above 500°F (260°C)\n- Damage from thermal shock (e.g., adding cold water to a very hot pot)\n- Damage from use on an incompatible cooking surface not listed in the manual\n- Wear and tear from normal use (e.g., minor surface scratches to the catcher's interior from use)\n- Consumable components that have been used as intended: crush washers (they deform by design), filter mesh replacement after extended use\n- Damage from unauthorized modification or repair\n- Damage from storage in conditions not consistent with normal household use\n- Cosmetic damage that does not affect function\n\n---\n\n## How to Make a Warranty Claim\n\n1. **Email** support@tallownative.com with the subject line \"Warranty Claim.\"\n2. **Include:** Your order number (or proof of purchase), your name and shipping address, a description of the defect, and at least two photographs of the defect.\n3. **We will respond within 3 business days** with a warranty determination and instructions.\n4. If the claim is approved: we will ship a replacement component or unit at no charge. We may request that you return the defective product (prepaid return label provided) or, for minor components, we may simply ship a replacement.\n\n**Claim deadline:** Claims must be made within the one-year Warranty Period. Claims received after the Warranty Period ends will not be honored under this warranty.\n\n---\n\n## Remedies\n\nAt Tallow Native's sole discretion, a warranted defect will be remedied by:\n- Replacement of the defective component\n- Replacement of the complete product\n- Refund of the purchase price (at Tallow Native's option for items that cannot be practically replaced)\n\n---\n\n## Post-Warranty Support\n\nAfter the one-year Warranty Period, Tallow Native will continue to offer replacement parts (crush washers, drain plugs, filter discs, gaskets, vent buttons) for sale. We are committed to making these consumables available as long as the product remains in production.\n\nContact support@tallownative.com for replacement part availability and pricing.\n\n---\n\n## Limitation of Liability\n\nTO THE MAXIMUM EXTENT PERMITTED BY APPLICABLE LAW, TALLOW NATIVE'S LIABILITY UNDER THIS WARRANTY IS LIMITED TO THE PURCHASE PRICE OF THE PRODUCT. TALLOW NATIVE IS NOT LIABLE FOR ANY INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL, OR CONSEQUENTIAL DAMAGES ARISING OUT OF OR RELATED TO THE PRODUCT, EVEN IF ADVISED OF THE POSSIBILITY OF SUCH DAMAGES.\n\n---\n\n## Your Statutory Rights\n\nThis warranty gives you specific legal rights. You may also have other rights which vary by state or jurisdiction. This warranty does not affect any statutory rights you may have.\n\n---\n\n## Contact\n\n**Warranty support:** support@tallownative.com  \n**Website:** tallownative.com  \n**Mailing address:** Tallow Native LLC, [Address], [City], Texas [ZIP]\n\n---\n\n*This warranty is issued by Tallow Native LLC and is valid only for products purchased directly from tallownative.com or authorized retail partners.*\n"
